ografie, an dem Vertreterinnen und Vertreter wichtiger deutscher und europäischer Institutionen beteiligt waren. Ergebnis dieser Netzwerkarbeit ist der vorliegende Band, der in die zentralen Arbeitsfelder der Internetlexikografie erstmals gesammelt einführt und den aktuellen Stand der wissenschaftlichen Forschung und lexikografischen Praxis vorstellt.  aThe internet has by now become the most important platform for publishing lexicographic content. In this volume, representatives from the Internet Lexicography network sponsored by the German Research Foundation provide the first-ever introduction to the central working areas of internet lexicography and present the current state of academic research and lexicographic practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aElectronic dictionaries. 0aGerman languagexData processing. 0aGerman languagexLexicography. 0aLexicographyxData processing. 4aDictionary research. 4aDictionary. 4aWörterbuch. 4aWörterbuchforschung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aKlosa, Annette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLoder, Martin1 aMüller-Spitzer, Carolin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2016z9783110485257oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103808420 cprintz978305006423940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978305009561540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783050095615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783050095615.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA